review_blob: This surprised the hell out of me. Looked great on the pour, not much on the nose but holy hell this has some taste. Bitter dark chocolate, coffee, some earth and oak in there too. Smokey on the finish. Great beer for a good price

Pours an earthy looking orange, almost like a rum and ginger beer. Nose is sweeter than I expected, very fruity. Taste is lemon citrus and slight funk and sour finish. Its refreshing on a warm humid day. Dig it.

First and foremost- what a cool bottle. Pours a pale yellow with a nice white head. Nose is lemon citrus, wet grass and funky. Taste is great. Lemon, funk, subtle hops, fruity, spicy. Quality drop on a summer evening

Pours dark black with a nice lasting tan head that lingers around the glass. Nose is vanilla dominated with some coffee, milk chocolate, sweet syrup. Taste is fantastic, strong but balanced and a thick but not heavy palate. Vanilla, coffee beans and some bitter slight chilli to finish. I just love this beer. Reminds me of a thicker victory at sea.
Its definitely creme brle. Also get some, spice, toffee, vanilla and chocolate. Nose is caramel, toffee and chocolate. Solid beer
beer_name: Emelisse Innovation Serie: Crme Brulee Stout

review_blob: Pours like a glowing honey with a nice white head. I get a lot of mandarin on the nose. Taste is bitter grapefruit, citrus, pine, bread. I wish I did this side by side with the original. I like it.

This is a pretty hard beer to pigeonhole. I think for mine it has a lot of similar elements to a BIPA just super complex and cool as fuck! I get lot of the dried fruit elements usually present in bourbon stouts as well as some earth and liquorice. Again so much going on but it works. Cracker of a beer. And for $11.
Pours black as black, slight white head. Definitely looks cola. Nose is loaded with sweet caramel and dark fruits - gives a real barley wine vibe for mine. Get the oaky bourbon finish. A good sipper
Really good beer, no one flavour really jumps out at you. Dark chocolate, woody/oak, leather, vanilla and some dark fruit i cant quite put my finger on. Quality beer

Pours black with a thin white head. Nose is loaded with cinnamon - basically a chai latte. Taste is very spice driven, cinnamon and gingerbread and faint vanilla. Pretty thin on the palate. Enjoyable for something a bit different
beer_name: Stone Imperial Russian Stout - Chai Spiced

review_blob: Love this!! Nose is chocolate, dry fruit, whisky booze. Taste is great balance of chocolate, raisins, earth, cola, caramel, vanilla and licorice and some sweet whisky booze. Fantastic beer, love it
Ive had this a few times and had mixed experiences. Pours dark. Aroma is fruity, vanilla, wood. Taste is coffee, cocoa, wood, booze, tobacco. I dig.

Wasnt really sure what to expect with this. 2013 bottle. Huge aroma on opening, lots of fruit, warm booze and vanilla. Taste is bitter vanilla and cocoa, mix of fruits - sultana, raisin, and plums. A lot better than I was expecting. Real enjoyable
Absolute dark fruit monster. Raisins, fruitcake, bourbon, hint of red wine. Really good beer.

I like pepper. Luckily. This is a pretty different beer but in a really cool way. So many different flavours in a serious stout - that work. I get the obvious pepper, dark chocolate, wood, spices but also some eucalyptus or mint or maybe new tennis ball haha. I like it
beer_name: Amager / Cigar City Xiquic And The Hero Twins

review_blob: i really like nearly everything thing about this beer. The subtle chilli, chocolatey spice. The look, the leathery smell. But theres just an overly sweet taste mid palate - caramel, plums mostly that is just a bit too much for me. Something about it isnt quite right - a real solid beer though.

I loved the aroma on this very rich chocolate/cocoa/vanilla. Taste is just a bit too bitter upfront, which has never really bothered me in a stout before. Strong vanilla, chocolate, woody notes with a slight caramel sweetness to finish. Solid beer

Pours a honey/dark brown with a small white head. Huge aromas of caramel/fruit/whisky. Taste is very similar with some toffee sweetness and sticky palate. I havent had/enjoyed many barley wines but really dig this!!
Bottle shared with timber and wazzy. Surprisingly lacks in aroma - but then again its like minus fifty outside. Love the taste, hoppy, malt, bread. Always good
beer_name: Firestone Walker Wookey Jack Black Rye IPA

review_blob: Pours black with a light tan head. Aroma is very cocoa/dark chocolate driven. Taste upfront is raisins, cocoa, coffee, smoke and a mint/bitter finish. I like it - nothing out of the ordinary but one ive enjoyed a few times now.

Pours nice enough, love the rich vanilla espresso on the nose. Taste is very vanilla dominated with coffee beans and a slightly leathery chocolate taste. I like vanilla beers and this is a well balanced quality beer, nothing out of the ordinary just solid.
On tap at DTC 4 July. Solid bitch. Grapefruit, bitter hops and super easy to drink. I dig
Bours black with a thick tan head. Nose is very grass, herbal, pine. Taste is malt, pine, coffee. I love the earthy feel to it - solid bro

I like this - nothing too exciting to look at and doesnt give too much away on the nose. Taste is super balanced and just a really enjoyable beer. Roasted malts, coffee, vanilla, earthy bitterness. I dig.
Bottle (rad one at that). Pours a bright gold with a very thick white head. Aroma is lemon citrus, spicy. Taste is a bit grassy, banana/mango, tart. Nice beer. Probably not really my style.
Pours a thin looking dark brown/black with a small white head. Nose is vanilla, caramel, fruity. Taste is vanilla, chocolate, oak, bourbon, dark fruit and some coconut. I love it
beer_name: De Molen Hel & Verdoemenis Misto BA

review_blob: Initial reaction to this was its hideously overrated. The more I drank the more I appreciated though. A little polarising in that I think my expectations based on its reputation didnt match up. But I did love the vanilla and liquorice bitterness. Just enjoy it for what it is
Wasnt sure what to expect on this. But shes a nice subtle enjoyable beer, nothing over the top. Vanilla, dark chocolate, cocoa, liquorice, wood and real subtle chilli

Pours a dark brown/black with white head. Nose is very fresh hops/earth/pine, vanilla and coffee. Taste is super fresh pine, grapefruit , vanilla with a bitter, subtle oak finish. Medium mouthfeel. Dont really notice the booze. Outstanding beer!!

I find this one hard to rate. Ive had it a few times and my opinion fluctuates wildly. Tonight I love it. Balanced flavours of vanilla, chocolate, roasted malts, slight bitterness, cocoa, coffee. Quality beer.

Pours dark with a pretty stingy white head. Aroma is a nice mix of malts, chocolate and a slight pine note. Taste is very much chocolate malts finish is slightly bitter but a bit weak and watery. Solid but nothing special.

Pours a murky copper/honey colour with a white head. Aroma is sweet and herbal. Taste is pretty similar with a slight sour oaky finish that turns into a sweet bourbon aftertaste. Not really my jam but a rock solid beer nonetheless
Yep cocoa! I like this, I was expecting sweet but got a nice bitter balanced beer loaded with cocoa, dark chocolate and vanilla. Boozy but not too boozy. A good bloke!

This surprised the shit out of me. Pours a thin black with a small tan head. Nose is very malt, chocolate earthy. The taste reminds me of something between eagle bay BIPA(minus the pine) and old Rasputin. Very roasted malt dominated, some coffee bean and vanilla. Deceptively drinkable. I dig
beer_name: Little Creatures Return of The Dread

review_blob: Blue wax bottle from mikkeller shop. Pours a heavy black with tan head. Nose is loaded with fruit, coffee, bourbon. Very thick sweet syrupy mouthfeel. Taste is coffee, vanilla, bourbon, chocolate and finishes very sweet. My only knock is its just a bit too sweet for me. Cracker beer and if you get the chance its a great beer to share with a mate or two (I chose not to share)
beer_name: Three Floyds Dark Lord Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: I hate this. Don't wanna be a dick but I also don't wanna rate this. I have a great tracksuit on.

Great beer. A looker too. Inviting black with mocha head. Huge espresso and oaky booze on the nose. Taste is a great balance of coffee, chocolate, smoke, booze and a great bitter piney finish. Never fails

Pours black with a small white head. Nose is very much cocoa, chocolate and some coffee vanilla notes. Taste is chocolate, slight vanilla bitterness, coffee. Nothing super sexy jumps out but its a seriously well balanced beer. Never fails!!

Pours black with a thick tan head that quickly settles. Nose is loaded with bourbon, dark fruits and spice. Taste is a sticky bourbon, oak, chocolate, fruits. A really great beer, far exceeded expectations. Hope I get to try again.

Pours black with a white slightly tan head. Nose is coffee and milk chocolate. Taste is loaded with powdered cocoa, dark chocolate and vanilla, with a bitter finish. Definitely above average. Solid, reliable and always good!!
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Pours a light orange with a raging white head. Nose is grassy, orange peel, citrus. Taste is crisp - citrus, pine, grapefruit. Didnt love it, but solid
I find brown ales to be either great or terrible. Sadly this is pretty terrible. Malt, caramel, biscuit, boring.
I really never expected to like this beer so much!! So well balanced. Caramel, oak, malt, chocolate, raisins, bourbon! Killer beer

Cracking beer. Nose is oaky booze, vanilla and chocolate. Taste is vanilla, coffee, malt and some earthy/spice/tobacco flavours. Can definitely pick up the oaky whisky. Great Aussie beer :) value for money too
beer_name: Boatrocker Ramjet Whisky Barrel Aged Imperial Stout

review_blob: Interesting beer. Comes out with all the fizzy characteristics of cola. Very funk/Brett driven. Some porter bitterness and some plum/cherry notes. Otherwise very belgiumy. Not bad

Pours jet black with a thick tan/cola head. Nose is amazing coffee, pine (smells a lot like black malts & body salts). Taste upfront is great espresso, grass, spice, cocoa, pine. Finish is the only slight negative, a bit sodaish. But a fan-f*cking-tastic beer!!!

So much going on with this beer. Pours an orange/copper colour. The nose is huge, sweet yeast, floral, grassy. Taste has some banana, floral, subtle funk, grass. Im not a huge fan of Belgian beers, but this is a cracker

Pours black with a small tan head. Aroma is loaded with bourbon booze, herb/fruit. Taste was super bourbon and vegemite, quite a barrage of flavours. Complex beer. Quality, but just didnt seem to balance the array of flavours
beer_name: De Molen Hel & Verdoemenis Wild Turkey BA

review_blob: Pours black with a small white/tan head. Nose is dark fruits, woody. Taste is really strong coffee and dark chocolate. Vanilla. Some subtle fruits, llicorice
